  NOTE — why L/tourist/day < hotel L/room/night coefficient:
  The denominator includes ALL tourist-days: day-trippers, pilgrims,
  VFR, business travellers — most of whom never stay in a classified
  hotel. Only ~50-80M hotel room-nights/yr exist vs 3-5 billion
  domestic tourist-days. The dilution is structural, not an error.
  To validate hotel coefficients independently, check:
    direct_twf_{year}.csv → Hotel_m3
  ÷ (classified_rooms × occupancy_rate × nights_per_year) in config.

